22// Use to compare the new values with the values already set in the command encoder:
23static inline bool operator==(const MTLViewport &lhs, const MTLViewport &rhs)
24{
25 return memcmp(&lhs, &rhs, sizeof(lhs)) == 0;
26}
27
28static inline bool operator==(const MTLScissorRect &lhs, const MTLScissorRect &rhs)
29{
30 return memcmp(&lhs, &rhs, sizeof(lhs)) == 0;

336void UseResourceCmd(id<MTLRenderCommandEncoder> encoder, IntermediateCommandStream *stream)
337{
338 auto resource = stream->fetch<id<MTLResource>>();
339 auto usage = stream->fetch<MTLResourceUsage>();
340 auto stages = stream->fetch<mtl::RenderStages>();
341 ANGLE_UNUSED_VARIABLE(stages);
342#if defined(__IPHONE_13_0) || defined(__MAC_10_15)
343 if (ANGLE_APPLE_AVAILABLE_XCI(10.15, 13.0, 13.0))
344 {
345 [encoder useResource:resource usage:usage stages:stages];
346 }
347 else
348#endif
349 {
350 [encoder useResource:resource usage:usage];
351 }
352 [resource ANGLE_MTL_RELEASE];
353}

359 auto after = stream->fetch<mtl::RenderStages>();

370 }

372 [resource ANGLE_MTL_RELEASE];

400NSString *cppLabelToObjC(const std::string &marker)
401{
402 auto label = [NSString stringWithUTF8String:marker.c_str()];
403 if (!label)
404 {
405 // This can happen if the string is not a valid ascii string.
406 label = @"Invalid ASCII string";
407 }
408 return label;
409}

425
426void CommandQueue::finishAllCommands()
427{
428 {
429 // Copy to temp list
430 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lg(mLock);
431
432 for (CmdBufferQueueEntry &metalBufferEntry : mMetalCmdBuffers)
433 {
434 mMetalCmdBuffersTmp.push_back(metalBufferEntry);
435 }
436
437 mMetalCmdBuffers.clear();
438 }
439
440 // Wait for command buffers to finish
441 for (CmdBufferQueueEntry &metalBufferEntry : mMetalCmdBuffersTmp)
442 {
443 [metalBufferEntry.buffer waitUntilCompleted];
444 }
445 mMetalCmdBuffersTmp.clear();
446}
447
448void CommandQueue::ensureResourceReadyForCPU(const ResourceRef &resource)
449{
450 if (!resource)
451 {
452 return;
453 }
454
455 ensureResourceReadyForCPU(resource.get());
456}
457
458void CommandQueue::ensureResourceReadyForCPU(Resource *resource)
459{
460 mLock.lock();
461 while (isResourceBeingUsedByGPU(resource) && !mMetalCmdBuffers.empty())
462 {
463 CmdBufferQueueEntry metalBufferEntry = mMetalCmdBuffers.front();
464 mMetalCmdBuffers.pop_front();
465 mLock.unlock();
466
467 ANGLE_MTL_LOG("Waiting for MTLCommandBuffer %llu:%p", metalBufferEntry.serial,
468 metalBufferEntry.buffer.get());
469 [metalBufferEntry.buffer waitUntilCompleted];
470
471 mLock.lock();
472 }
473 mLock.unlock();
474
475 // This can happen if the resource is read then write in the same command buffer.
476 // So it is the responsitibily of outer code to ensure the command buffer is commit before
477 // the resource can be read or written again
478 ASSERT(!isResourceBeingUsedByGPU(resource));
479}
480
481bool CommandQueue::isResourceBeingUsedByGPU(const Resource *resource) const
482{
483 if (!resource)
484 {
485 return false;
486 }
487
488 return mCompletedBufferSerial.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) <
489 resource->getCommandBufferQueueSerial();
490}
491
492bool CommandQueue::resourceHasPendingWorks(const Resource *resource) const
493{
494 if (!resource)
495 {
496 return false;
497 }
498
499 return mCommittedBufferSerial.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) <
500 resource->getCommandBufferQueueSerial();
501}
502
503AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLCommandBuffer>> CommandQueue::makeMetalCommandBuffer(uint64_t *queueSerialOut)
504{
505 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
506 {
507 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLCommandBuffer>> metalCmdBuffer = [get() commandBuffer];
508
509 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lg(mLock);
510
511 uint64_t serial = mQueueSerialCounter++;
512
513 mMetalCmdBuffers.push_back({metalCmdBuffer, serial});
514
515 ANGLE_MTL_LOG("Created MTLCommandBuffer %llu:%p", serial, metalCmdBuffer.get());
516
517 [metalCmdBuffer addCompletedHandler:^(id<MTLCommandBuffer> buf) {
518 onCommandBufferCompleted(buf, serial);
519 }];
520
521 [metalCmdBuffer enqueue];
522
523 ASSERT(metalCmdBuffer);
524
525 *queueSerialOut = serial;
526
527 return metalCmdBuffer;
528 }
529}
530
531void CommandQueue::onCommandBufferCommitted(id<MTLCommandBuffer> buf, uint64_t serial)
532{
533 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lg(mLock);
534
535 ANGLE_MTL_LOG("Committed MTLCommandBuffer %llu:%p", serial, buf);
536
537 mCommittedBufferSerial.store(
538 std::max(mCommittedBufferSerial.load(std::memory_order_relaxed), serial),
539 std::memory_order_relaxed);
540}
541
542void CommandQueue::onCommandBufferCompleted(id<MTLCommandBuffer> buf, uint64_t serial)
543{
544 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lg(mLock);
545
546 ANGLE_MTL_LOG("Completed MTLCommandBuffer %llu:%p", serial, buf);
547
548 if (mCompletedBufferSerial >= serial)
549 {
550 // Already handled.
551 return;
552 }
553
554 while (!mMetalCmdBuffers.empty() && mMetalCmdBuffers.front().serial <= serial)
555 {
556 CmdBufferQueueEntry metalBufferEntry = mMetalCmdBuffers.front();
557 ANGLE_UNUSED_VARIABLE(metalBufferEntry);
558 ANGLE_MTL_LOG("Popped MTLCommandBuffer %llu:%p", metalBufferEntry.serial,
559 metalBufferEntry.buffer.get());
560
561 mMetalCmdBuffers.pop_front();
562 }
563
564 mCompletedBufferSerial.store(
565 std::max(mCompletedBufferSerial.load(std::memory_order_relaxed), serial),
566 std::memory_order_relaxed);
567}

585void CommandBuffer::commit(CommandBufferFinishOperation operation)
586{
587 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lg(mLock);
588 commitImpl();
589 if(operation == WaitUntilScheduled)
590 {
591 [get() waitUntilScheduled];
592 }
593 else if(operation == WaitUntilFinished)
594 {
595 [get() waitUntilCompleted];
596 }
597}

645void CommandBuffer::restart()
646{
647 uint64_t serial = 0;
648 auto metalCmdBuffer = mCmdQueue.makeMetalCommandBuffer(&serial);
649
650 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lg(mLock);
651
652 set(metalCmdBuffer);
653 mQueueSerial = serial;
654 mCommitted = false;
655
656 for (std::string &marker : mDebugGroups)
657 {
658 pushDebugGroupImpl(marker);
659 }
660
661 ASSERT(metalCmdBuffer);
662}

691void CommandBuffer::queueEventSignal(const mtl::SharedEventRef &event, uint64_t value)
692{
693 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lg(mLock);
694
695 ASSERT(validImpl());
696
697 if (mActiveCommandEncoder && mActiveCommandEncoder->getType() == CommandEncoder::RENDER)
698 {
699 // We cannot set event when there is an active render pass, defer the setting until the
700 // pass end.
701 mPendingSignalEvents.push_back({event, value});
702 }
703 else
704 {
705 setEventImpl(event, value);
706 }
707}

709void CommandBuffer::serverWaitEvent(const mtl::SharedEventRef &event, uint64_t value)
710{
711 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lg(mLock);
712 ASSERT(validImpl());
713
714 waitEventImpl(event, value);
715}

723void CommandBuffer::setActiveCommandEncoder(CommandEncoder *encoder)
724{
725 mActiveCommandEncoder = encoder;
726 for (auto &marker : mPendingDebugSigns)
727 {
728 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE

734 mPendingDebugSigns.clear();

737void CommandBuffer::invalidateActiveCommandEncoder(CommandEncoder *encoder)
738{
739 if (mActiveCommandEncoder == encoder)
740 {
741 mActiveCommandEncoder = nullptr;
742
743 // No active command encoder, we can safely encode event signalling now.
744 setPendingEvents();
745 }
746}

748void CommandBuffer::cleanup()
749{
750 mActiveCommandEncoder = nullptr;
751
752 ParentClass::set(nil);
753}
754
755bool CommandBuffer::validImpl() const
756{
757 if (!ParentClass::valid())
758 {
759 return false;
760 }
761
762 return !mCommitted;
763}
764
765void CommandBuffer::commitImpl()
766{
767 if (!validImpl())
768 {
769 return;
770 }
771
772 // End the current encoder
773 forceEndingCurrentEncoder();
774
775 // Encoding any pending event's signalling.
776 setPendingEvents();
777
778 // Notify command queue
779 mCmdQueue.onCommandBufferCommitted(get(), mQueueSerial);
780
781 // Do the actual commit
782 [get() commit];
783 mCommitted = true;
784}
785
786void CommandBuffer::forceEndingCurrentEncoder()
787{
788 if (mActiveCommandEncoder)
789 {
790 mActiveCommandEncoder->endEncoding();
791 mActiveCommandEncoder = nullptr;
792 }
793}

795void CommandBuffer::setPendingEvents()
796{
797#if ANGLE_MTL_EVENT_AVAILABLE
798 for (const std::pair<mtl::SharedEventRef, uint64_t> &eventEntry : mPendingSignalEvents)
799 {
800 setEventImpl(eventEntry.first, eventEntry.second);
801 }
802 mPendingSignalEvents.clear();
803#endif
804}
805
806void CommandBuffer::setEventImpl(const mtl::SharedEventRef &event, uint64_t value)
807{
808#if ANGLE_MTL_EVENT_AVAILABLE

1041void RenderCommandEncoder::finalizeLoadStoreAction(
1042 MTLRenderPassAttachmentDescriptor *objCRenderPassAttachment)
1043{
1044 if (!objCRenderPassAttachment.texture)
1045 {
1046 objCRenderPassAttachment.loadAction = MTLLoadActionDontCare;
1047 objCRenderPassAttachment.storeAction = MTLStoreActionDontCare;
1048 objCRenderPassAttachment.resolveTexture = nil;
1049 return;
1050 }
1051
1052 if (objCRenderPassAttachment.resolveTexture)
1053 {
1054 if (objCRenderPassAttachment.storeAction == MTLStoreActionStore)
1055 {
1056 // NOTE(hqle): Currently if the store action with implicit MS texture is MTLStoreAction,
1057 // it is automatically convert to store and resolve action. It might introduce
1058 // unnecessary overhead.
1059 // Consider an improvement such as only store the MS texture, and resolve only at
1060 // the end of real render pass (not render pass the was interrupted by compute pass)
1061 // or before glBlitFramebuffer operation starts.
1062 objCRenderPassAttachment.storeAction = MTLStoreActionStoreAndMultisampleResolve;
1063 }
1064 else if (objCRenderPassAttachment.storeAction == MTLStoreActionDontCare)
1065 {
1066 // Ignore resolve texture if the store action is not a resolve action.
1067 objCRenderPassAttachment.resolveTexture = nil;
1068 }
1069 }
1070
1071 if (objCRenderPassAttachment.storeAction == MTLStoreActionUnknown)
1072 {
1073 // If storeAction hasn't been set for this attachment, we set to dontcare.
1074 objCRenderPassAttachment.storeAction = MTLStoreActionDontCare;
1075 }
1076}

1078void RenderCommandEncoder::endEncoding()
1079{
1080 endEncodingImpl(true);
1081}
1082
1083void RenderCommandEncoder::endEncodingImpl(bool considerDiscardSimulation)
1084{
1085 if (!valid())
1086 return;
1087
1088 // Last minute correcting the store options.
1089 MTLRenderPassDescriptor *objCRenderPassDesc = mCachedRenderPassDescObjC.get();
1090 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < mRenderPassDesc.numColorAttachments; ++i)
1091 {
1092 // Update store action set between restart() and endEncoding()
1093 objCRenderPassDesc.colorAttachments[i].storeAction =
1094 mRenderPassDesc.colorAttachments[i].storeAction;
1095 finalizeLoadStoreAction(objCRenderPassDesc.colorAttachments[i]);
1096 }
1097
1098 // Update store action set between restart() and endEncoding()
1099 objCRenderPassDesc.depthAttachment.storeAction = mRenderPassDesc.depthAttachment.storeAction;
1100 finalizeLoadStoreAction(objCRenderPassDesc.depthAttachment);
1101
1102 // Update store action set between restart() and endEncoding()
1103 objCRenderPassDesc.stencilAttachment.storeAction =
1104 mRenderPassDesc.stencilAttachment.storeAction;
1105 finalizeLoadStoreAction(objCRenderPassDesc.stencilAttachment);
1106
1107 // Set visibility result buffer
1108 if (mOcclusionQueryPool.getNumRenderPassAllocatedQueries())
1109 {
1110 objCRenderPassDesc.visibilityResultBuffer =
1111 mOcclusionQueryPool.getRenderPassVisibilityPoolBuffer()->get();
1112 }
1113 else
1114 {
1115 objCRenderPassDesc.visibilityResultBuffer = nil;
1116 }
1117
1118 // Encode the actual encoder
1119 encodeMetalEncoder();
1120
1121 CommandEncoder::endEncoding();
1122
1123#if ANGLE_MTL_SIMULATE_DISCARD_FRAMEBUFFER
1124 if (considerDiscardSimulation)
1125 {
1126 simulateDiscardFramebuffer();
1127 }
1128#endif
1129
1130 // reset state
1131 mRenderPassDesc = RenderPassDesc();
1132 mStateCache.reset();
1133}

1161void RenderCommandEncoder::simulateDiscardFramebuffer()
1162{
1163 // Simulate true framebuffer discard operation by clearing the framebuffer
1164#if ANGLE_MTL_SIMULATE_DISCARD_FRAMEBUFFER
1165 std::random_device rd; // Will be used to obtain a seed for the random number engine
1166 std::mt19937 gen(rd()); // Standard mersenne_twister_engine seeded with rd()
1167 std::uniform_real_distribution<float> dis(0.0, 1.0f);
1168 bool hasDiscard = false;
1169 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < mRenderPassDesc.numColorAttachments; ++i)
1170 {
1171 if (mRenderPassDesc.colorAttachments[i].storeAction == MTLStoreActionDontCare)
1172 {
1173 hasDiscard = true;
1174 mRenderPassDesc.colorAttachments[i].loadAction = MTLLoadActionClear;
1175 mRenderPassDesc.colorAttachments[i].clearColor =
1176 MTLClearColorMake(dis(gen), dis(gen), dis(gen), dis(gen));
1177 }
1178 else
1179 {
1180 mRenderPassDesc.colorAttachments[i].loadAction = MTLLoadActionLoad;
1181 }
1182 }
1183
1184 if (mRenderPassDesc.depthAttachment.storeAction == MTLStoreActionDontCare)
1185 {
1186 hasDiscard = true;
1187 mRenderPassDesc.depthAttachment.loadAction = MTLLoadActionClear;
1188 mRenderPassDesc.depthAttachment.clearDepth = dis(gen);
1189 }
1190 else
1191 {
1192 mRenderPassDesc.depthAttachment.loadAction = MTLLoadActionLoad;
1193 }
1194
1195 if (mRenderPassDesc.stencilAttachment.storeAction == MTLStoreActionDontCare)
1196 {
1197 hasDiscard = true;
1198 mRenderPassDesc.stencilAttachment.loadAction = MTLLoadActionClear;
1199 mRenderPassDesc.stencilAttachment.clearStencil = rand();
1200 }
1201 else
1202 {
1203 mRenderPassDesc.stencilAttachment.loadAction = MTLLoadActionLoad;
1204 }
1205
1206 if (hasDiscard)
1207 {
1208 auto tmpDesc = mRenderPassDesc;
1209 restart(tmpDesc);
1210 endEncodingImpl(false);
1211 }
1212#endif // ANGLE_MTL_SIMULATE_DISCARD_FRAMEBUFFER
1213}
1214
1215void RenderCommandEncoder::encodeMetalEncoder()
1216{
1217 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
1218 {
1219 ANGLE_MTL_LOG("Creating new render command encoder with desc: %@",
1220 [mCachedRenderPassDescObjC description]);
1221
1222 id<MTLRenderCommandEncoder> metalCmdEncoder =
1223 [cmdBuffer().get() renderCommandEncoderWithDescriptor:mCachedRenderPassDescObjC];
1224
1225 set(metalCmdEncoder);
1226
1227 // Verify that it was created successfully
1228 ASSERT(get());
1229
1230 // Work-around driver bug on iOS devices: stencil must be explicitly set to zero
1231 // even if the doc says the default value is already zero.
1232 [metalCmdEncoder setStencilReferenceValue:0];
1233
1234 if (mLabel)
1235 {
1236 metalCmdEncoder.label = mLabel;
1237 }
1238
1239 while (mCommands.good())
1240 {
1241 auto cmdType = mCommands.fetch<CmdType>();
1242 CommandEncoderFunc encoder = gCommandEncoders[static_cast<int>(cmdType)];
1243 encoder(metalCmdEncoder, &mCommands);
1244 }
1245
1246 mCommands.clear();
1247 }
1248}
1249
1250RenderCommandEncoder &RenderCommandEncoder::restart(const RenderPassDesc &desc)
1251{
1252 if (valid())
1253 {
1254 if (mRenderPassDesc == desc)
1255 {
1256 // no change, skip
1257 return *this;
1258 }
1259
1260 // finish current encoder
1261 endEncoding();
1262 }
1263
1264 if (!cmdBuffer().valid())
1265 {
1266 reset();
1267 return *this;
1268 }
1269
1270 mRenderPassDesc = desc;
1271 mRecording = true;
1272 mHasDrawCalls = false;
1273 mRenderPassMaxScissorRect = {.x = 0,
1274 .y = 0,
1275 .width = std::numeric_limits<NSUInteger>::max(),
1276 .height = std::numeric_limits<NSUInteger>::max()};
1277 // mask writing dependency & set appropriate store options
1278 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < mRenderPassDesc.numColorAttachments; ++i)
1279 {
1280 initAttachmentWriteDependencyAndScissorRect(mRenderPassDesc.colorAttachments[i]);
1281 }
1282
1283 initAttachmentWriteDependencyAndScissorRect(mRenderPassDesc.depthAttachment);
1284
1285 initAttachmentWriteDependencyAndScissorRect(mRenderPassDesc.stencilAttachment);
1286
1287 // Convert to Objective-C descriptor
1288 mRenderPassDesc.convertToMetalDesc(mCachedRenderPassDescObjC);
1289
1290 // The actual Objective-C encoder will be created later in endEncoding(), we do so in order
1291 // to be able to sort the commands or do the preprocessing before the actual encoding.
1292
1293 // Since we defer the native encoder creation, we need to explicitly tell command buffer that
1294 // this object is the active encoder:
1295 cmdBuffer().setActiveCommandEncoder(this);
1296
1297 return *this;
1298}

1431 return *this;

1491RenderCommandEncoder &RenderCommandEncoder::commonSetBuffer(gl::ShaderType shaderType,
1492 id<MTLBuffer> mtlBuffer,
1493 uint32_t offset,
1494 uint32_t index)
1495{
1496 RenderCommandEncoderShaderStates &shaderStates = mStateCache.perShaderStates[shaderType];
1497 if (shaderStates.buffers[index] == mtlBuffer)
1498 {
1499 if (shaderStates.bufferOffsets[index] == offset)
1500 {
1501 return *this;
1502 }
1503
1504 // If buffer already bound but with different offset, then update the offer only.
1505 shaderStates.bufferOffsets[index] = offset;
1506
1507 mCommands.push(static_cast<CmdType>(mSetBufferOffsetCmds[shaderType]))
1508 .push(offset)
1509 .push(index);
1510
1511 return *this;
1512 }
1513
1514 shaderStates.buffers[index] = mtlBuffer;
1515 shaderStates.bufferOffsets[index] = offset;
1516
1517 mCommands.push(static_cast<CmdType>(mSetBufferCmds[shaderType]))
1518 .push([mtlBuffer ANGLE_MTL_RETAIN])
1519 .push(offset)
1520 .push(index);
1521
1522 return *this;
1523}
1524
1525RenderCommandEncoder &RenderCommandEncoder::setBytes(gl::ShaderType shaderType,
1526 const uint8_t *bytes,
1527 size_t size,
1528 uint32_t index)
1529{
1530 if (index >= kMaxShaderBuffers)
1531 {
1532 return *this;
1533 }
1534
1535 RenderCommandEncoderShaderStates &shaderStates = mStateCache.perShaderStates[shaderType];
1536 shaderStates.buffers[index] = nil;
1537 shaderStates.bufferOffsets[index] = 0;
1538
1539 mCommands.push(static_cast<CmdType>(mSetBytesCmds[shaderType]))
1540 .push(size)
1541 .push(bytes, size)

1547RenderCommandEncoder &RenderCommandEncoder::setSamplerState(gl::ShaderType shaderType,
1548 id<MTLSamplerState> state,
1549 float lodMinClamp,
1550 float lodMaxClamp,
1551 uint32_t index)
1552{
1553 if (index >= kMaxShaderSamplers)
1554 {
1555 return *this;
1556 }
1557
1558 RenderCommandEncoderShaderStates &shaderStates = mStateCache.perShaderStates[shaderType];
1559 if (shaderStates.samplers[index] == state && shaderStates.samplerLodClamps[index].valid())
1560 {
1561 const std::pair<float, float> &currentLodClampRange =
1562 shaderStates.samplerLodClamps[index].value();
1563 if (currentLodClampRange.first == lodMinClamp && currentLodClampRange.second == lodMaxClamp)
1564 {
1565 return *this;
1566 }
1567 }
1568
1569 shaderStates.samplers[index] = state;
1570 shaderStates.samplerLodClamps[index] = {lodMinClamp, lodMaxClamp};
1571
1572 mCommands.push(static_cast<CmdType>(mSetSamplerCmds[shaderType]))
1573 .push([state ANGLE_MTL_RETAIN])
1574 .push(lodMinClamp)
1575 .push(lodMaxClamp)
1576 .push(index);
1577
1578 return *this;
